ObjectClass.preferredDefinition: An assessment of the physical condition of an infant at the time birth; involves heart rate, muscle tone, respiratory effort,  color, and reflex responsiveness.

Concepts.definition: The numerical sum between zero and ten that is computed from individual values of zero to two that are assigned to five different areas of interest in newborn screenings. These areas are breathing, muscle tone, pulse rate, reflex irritability and skin color.
